
🔤 isupper() & islower()
ch = "A"  

ch.isupper()  # True
ch.islower()  # False  

✔️ Usage:

isupper() → checks if character is uppercase 

islower() → checks if character is lowercase

🧮 collections.Counter Example
from collections import Counter

s = "abc"
cnt = Counter(s)

print(cnt["a"])  # 1
print(cnt["b"])  # 1
print(cnt["c"])  # 1
print(cnt["d"])  # 0  -> missing keys return 0

✔️ Key Points:

Counts the frequency of characters

If a key does not exist, Counter returns 0

